	"description": "Your Swimmer Type: Stroke Fader\n\nWorking on your technique during short, low intensity intervals is vital to holding your technique when you increase your intensity for longer sets.\n\nPracticing technique at the beginning of the workout will help you establish, and improve, your technique will give you a great starting point.\n\nFor this workout, the relatively short, but strong, intervals will challenge you to hold your technique as you increase your effort, especially towards the end when you are more tired.\n\nUsing equipment is always optional, but here the equipment will help you focus just on your technique, rather than the difficulty of the workout.",
